        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh adds bounded projection coverage for channel setup rows, provider discovery fallbacks beside runtime manifest catalogs, loader cache-key metadata, plugin registry alias reads, provider tool schema arrays, configured model catalog API reads, and the recent mainline conflict surfaces\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `4b2d92ba27885d7c2795f8816a503d38cecb0c6b`\n- GitHub reports the PR as mergeable against current base `439c09668ea7d5cf8804a4d20cd90a10055bf1ad`; final local proof ran after a clean rebase on `origin/main` at `6804b7cb716b79c0264375f3c41bb290d7727138`, before `main` advanced again\n\n## Verification\n\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/loader.runtime-registry.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts src/plugins/channel-plugin-ids.test.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 2 Vitest shards passed; 3 unit-fast files / 51 tests and 4 plugin files / 195 tests\n- `env CI=1 perl -e 'alarm shift; exec @ARGV' 180 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/model-catalog.test.ts --reporter=verbose -t \"dedupes configured models without rewriting provider ids\"`: 2 files passed, 2 tests passed, 72 skipped\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/model-selection-shared.ts src/plugins/loader.ts src/plugins/loader.runtime-registry.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry-id-normalizer.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts src/plugins/channel-plugin-ids.test.ts src/plugins/gateway-startup-plugin-ids.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/plugins/provider-plugin-projection.ts src/plugins/providers.runtime.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/model-selection-shared.ts src/plugins/loader.ts src/plugins/loader.runtime-registry.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.ts src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.ts src/agents/schema/clean-for-gemini.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry-id-normalizer.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts src/plugins/channel-plugin-ids.test.ts src/plugins/gateway-startup-plugin-ids.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.ts src/plugins/provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts src/plugins/provider-plugin-projection.ts src/plugins/providers.runtime.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.ts src/flows/channel-setup.status.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- scrubbed the branch diff and PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths: clean\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean after adding the provider-discovery fallback/runtime-manifest regression\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run -provider blacksmith-testbox -shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`: blocked before remote execution because Blacksmith is not authenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required)\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, provider/runtime/channel/plugin registry projections, model/provider install catalog projections, provider discovery projection, web search install catalog projection, model picker provider catalog projection, web search setup provider projection, provider model-picker flow projection, provider setup flow projection, provider runtime hook-ref projection, channel setup selection projection, and configured model catalog projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable env vars, unreadable install/provider metadata, unreadable catalog hooks, unreadable setup provider rows, unreadable setup choices, unreadable channel setup rows, unreadable model-picker contribution rows, or unreadable configured model API rows while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, current head `4b2d92ba27885d7c2795f8816a503d38cecb0c6b`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: rebased cleanly onto `origin/main` at `6804b7cb716b79c0264375f3c41bb290d7727138`, ran the focused Vitest shard set for loader/provider-tools/Gemini/schema registry/provider-discovery/channel setup, ran the configured model catalog target, ran formatting, linting, commit diff check, private-name scrub, and attempted the Blacksmith-backed changed gate listed in Verification.\n\nEvidence after fix: `channel-setup.status.test.ts` seeds an unreadable `fuzzplugin` setup entry while proving the healthy `mockplugin` setup choice remains visible. `provider-discovery.runtime.test.ts` covers unreadable discovery-entry providers, manifest catalog preservation beside fallback loads, entries-only completeness for mixed static/runtime catalogs, and the case where failed projection plugins must stay in fallback loading beside runtime manifest catalog plugins. `model-catalog.test.ts` covers configured model catalog dedupe after bounded configured-model reads.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed channel setup metadata no longer aborts setup contribution construction before healthy rows are reached; malformed provider discovery entries no longer drop healthy provider rows or omit required fallback full-load plugin ids when runtime manifest catalog plugins are also involved; unreadable configured model catalog fields are read through the same bounded projection path before catalog rows are emitted.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate did not run because the local Blacksmith CLI is unauthenticated (`blacksmith auth login` required). AWS Crabbox broad gate was not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted local shard set plus formatter/lint/diff/scrub/autoreview checks.\n",
